// Virtual main: exit code = idiom_present() + bind_present() == 1 + 5 == 6. Reaching it forces
// the WHOLE work.tks (every optional sub-feature: the error? idiom, a T? binding+match, a
// fn -> T? null, ?. + ??) through the checker, VM and codegen. A clean exit 6 on BOTH the VM
// (`teko run`) and the compiled binary (`teko build`) proves the optionals subsystem holds.
use m

(m::idiom_present() + m::bind_present()) to i32
